    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-05-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="181" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 575.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 4, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 17th of April (No.
                            379) has been received. The promptness with which you have laid before
                            the government of Great Britain the facts ascertained by you in regard
                            to the unlawful equipment and departure of the Virginia, is appreciated,
                            and the President indulges a confident expectation that that government
                            will do all that may be within its power to avert from the international
                            commerce the danger which the transaction menaces, and to prevent
                            similar transactions in future.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
